/**
 * Gives a single-word string description of the (native) type of a value, returning such answers as 'Object', 'Number', 'Array', or 'Null'. Does not attempt to distinguish user Object types any further, reporting them all as 'Object'.
 *

 *
 * P.type({}); //=> "Object" P.type(1); //=> "Number" P.type(false); //=> "Boolean" P.type('s'); //=> "String" P.type(null); //=> "Null" P.type([]); //=> "Array" P.type(/[A-z]/); //=> "RegExp" P.type(() => {}); //=> "Function" P.type(undefined); //=> "Undefined" P.type(new Date()); //=> "Date" P.type(new MyClass()); // => "MyClass"  @category Utility
 */
